<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2419] Improve parallel tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2419</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;As mentioned on the dev@ mailing list here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.lucidimagination.com/search/document/93432a677917b9bd/lucenejunitresultformatter_sometimes_fails_to_lock&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://www.lucidimagination.com/search/document/93432a677917b9bd/lucenejunitresultformatter_sometimes_fails_to_lock&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to not create a lockfactory for each test suite (As they are run sequentially in the same separate JVM).&lt;br/&gt;
Additionally, we create a lot of JVMs (26) for each batch, because we have to run one for each letter.&lt;br/&gt;
Instead, we use a technique here to divide up the tests with a custom selector: &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.code-cop.org/2009/09/parallel-junit.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://blog.code-cop.org/2009/09/parallel-junit.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
(I emailed the blog author and received permission to use this code)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This gives a nice boost to the speed of overall tests, especially Solr tests, as many start with an &quot;S&quot;, but this is no longer a problem.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
